Bambang is a 38 year old freight driver. He has been doing this job for almost 12 years. He bought a second-hand car to be operated as a freight car. Bambang is married and has 5 children. They are: 
-	Tia, 14 years old who is in the 2nd grade of Junior high school; 
-	Rivai, 12 years old who is in the 1st grade of Junior high school; 
-	Bima, 9 years old who is in the 3rd grade of elementary school; 
-	Trisha, 4 years old; and 
-	Panca, 1 and a half year old. 
Bambang and his family live in Pasir Panjang Village.

Bambang usually looks for customers in Kupang City. He usually parks his car in front of a basic foods shop in Kupang and waits for the customers who need his service to deliver the goods that they bought. His income as a driver is unstable and depends on how many customerst he gets within a day. He can generate about IDR 75,000 to 250,000 in a day. But there are also times when he has to return home without any income. Moreover, his car often has problems so he has to stop working for a few days just to fix the car. There are some spare parts of the car that have to be replaced, but because the price is expensive, Bambang cannot afford it. He replaced the spare parts with cheaper ones, but the repair did not last for long. For this reason, Bambang is requesting a loan amounting to IDR 4,500,000 from TLM. He really hopes to get the loan so he can buy the new spare parts for his car.
